description.p:
According to other features of the method according to the invention:
the cleanable liquid is alcohol, still water, carbonated water or a detergent liquid;
the concentrated liquid is a concentrated liquid containing sugar and/or an aroma;
the concentrated liquid has a viscosity greater than and different from the viscosity of water;
the concentrated liquid further comprises a particulate material;
the size of the particles of the particulate material is greater than 1 mm;
the concentrated liquid is a syrup.
the forming station 4 is moved in rotation around a first axis during the forming step and the concentrate filling station 6 is moved in rotation around a second axis, different from the first axis and substantially parallel to said first axis, during the step of filling the concentrated liquid;
the concentrated liquid is a premix made of a mixing of a concentrate with a quantity of liquid, said premix having a volumetric concentrate concentration, and the end volume of end product filled in the container is the sum of a first volume of said cleanable liquid injected by the forming station 4 and of a second volume of said premix filled in the same container by the concentrate filling station 6, the liquid forming the premix being preferably made of the same liquid material than the material of said cleanable liquid.

According to other features of the machine according to the invention:
the machine comprises placing means arranged for placing a preform in the forming station and transferring means arranged for transferring the formed container already containing cleanable liquid from the forming station to the concentrate filling station;
the forming station is attached to a forming wheel moving in rotation around a first axis and the concentrate filling station is attached to a second wheel moving in rotation around a second axis, different from the first axis and substantially parallel to the first axis;
the forming wheel carries a plurality of forming stations 4 and the second wheel carries a plurality of concentrate filling stations such that the machine can simultaneously form and fill a plurality of preforms into containers and inject the concentrated liquid into a plurality of filled containers;
the transferring means include a mechanism for reducing the pitch between two successive transferred containers while said two successive transferred containers move from the forming station to the concentrate filling station.
